23_description:
Additional terms apply. Users may not:
  • abridge, modify, translate or create any derivative work based on Elsevier content, except to summarize factual information and link to the source where the information originates with a citation in compliance with relevant Wikipedia policies.
  • remove, obscure or modify in any way any copyright notices, other notices, or disclaimers
  • use any robots, spiders, crawlers or other automated downloading programs, algorithms or devices to continuously and automatically search, scrape, extract, deep link, index or disrupt the working of the website
  • substantially or systematically reproduce, retain, store locally, redistribute or disseminate Elsevier content online
  • post individual items on social networking sites.

43_description: Editors should ensure that all material used for Wikipedia purposes meets the criteria of the relevant reliable sources policy. • Academic OneFile, a database of more than 17,000 periodicals, including 3,000 peer-reviewed scholarly journals.

26_description: When citing Newspapers.com content, use clippings where possible. Clippings allow readers to view the source text through an open access URL without having to subscribe.
